- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is also likely as the paper deals with logics of knowledge and their computational frameworks. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is relevant as the paper uses logic programming to encode logics of knowledge and compute Kripke models. 
- cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) is relevant as the paper deals with multi-agent planning with knowledge actions and degrees of visibility. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is less likely but still possible as the paper may discuss the computational complexity of the proposed approach.
